OL,3,CTwo-thirds of young people think
OL,4,Cvaping is 'socially acceptable'
OL,6,FAttitudes towards vaping and smoking
OL,7,Fchange significantly across different
OL,8,Fage groups, according to new research.
OL,10,FA survey of more than 4,300 islanders
OL,11,Facross Guernsey, Jersey, Gibraltar,
OL,12,Fand the Isle of Man by Island Global
OL,13,FResearch found that younger people
OL,14,Faged 18 to 39 were more likely to
OL,15,Fbelieve vaping outside in public was a
OL,16,Fsocially acceptable behaviour.
OL,18,FAcross this age group, 63% of
OL,19,Frespondents in Jersey and 70% in
OL,20,FGuernsey expressed this belief.
