OL,3,CTwo-thirds of young people think
OL,4,Cvaping is 'socially acceptable'
OL,6,FConversely, those in the 65+ age
OL,7,Fbracket were significantly less likely
OL,8,Fto view vaping in public this way,
OL,9,Faround a quarter in both Channel
OL,10,FIslands.
OL,12,FHowever, the survey found strong
OL,13,Fsupport for measures designed to
OL,14,Fspecifically deter young people from
OL,15,Fvaping.
OL,17,FWhilst 41% of respondents in Jersey
OL,18,Fand 40% in Guernsey believed that more
OL,19,Fshould be done to reduce harm caused
OL,20,Fby smoking, these numbers rose to 45%
OL,21,Fand 46% with respect to vaping.
