OL,3,CTwo-thirds of young people think
OL,4,Cvaping is 'socially acceptable'
OL,6,FTwo-thirds of Jersey respondents and
OL,7,F72% of those surveyed in Guernsey
OL,8,Fsupport the introduction of a vape tax
OL,9,F- such as the one proposed in
OL,10,FGuernsey's Budget.
OL,12,FThe majority of respondents across
OL,13,Fboth islands also expressed support
OL,14,Ffor measures such as banning flavoured
OL,15,Fvapes, introducing public health
OL,16,Fcampaigns targeted at young people,
OL,17,Fand bringing in a 'phased out'
OL,18,Fapproach that would ban vaping for
OL,19,Fthose born after 2009.
